-- Heathrow appoints John Holland-Kaye as new CEO
-- 
-- Thu May 08, 2014 05:11AM EDT
-- None



May 8 (Reuters) - London's Heathrow Airport has promoted its development director John Holland-Kaye to the chief executive position, replacing Colin Matthews who announced his departure in April.

Heathrow, the world's third busiest airport, said Holland-Kaye would take over as chief executive from July 1. Heathrow's owners include Spain's Ferrovial <FER.MC> and the sovereign wealth funds of Qatar, China and Singapore.